==English==
===Etymology===
A 19th-century US coinage, probably based on [[discompose]], [[discomfit]], etc.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/dɪskəm'bɒbjʊleɪt/}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|discombobulate|discombobulates|discombobulated|discombobulating}}
#{{transitive}} (''Humorous'') To [[throw]] into a [[state]] of [[confusion]]; to [[befuddle]] or [[perplex]].

